# Local-run config. In production these are split:
#   - non-secret per-tier config  → committed in deploy/dev.env and deploy/prod.env
#   - secret + per-tier subdir     → set per resource in Coolify (SLACK_BOT_TOKEN, MEMES_DIR)
#   - tier selector               → TIER (dev|prod), picks which deploy/<tier>.env to load
#
# To run locally:  cp .env.sample .env   (docker compose auto-loads .env for ${...})
# Note: the compose binds the apps-01 path /mnt/dropbox/Archive/Funny:/funny — for a
# local run, change that volume line (or create the path) and set MEMES_DIR below.

# Which committed config file to load (deploy/dev.env or deploy/prod.env):
TIER=dev

# Memes folder INSIDE the container — a subdir of the bound parent (/funny).
# Coolify: /funny/Programming-Dev (dev) | /funny/Programming (prod).
MEMES_DIR=/funny/Programming-Dev

# Bot User OAuth Token (xoxb-...). Secret — never commit. See CreateSlackBot.md.
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=
